36#ifdef __NetBSD__
37static int
38compare_dmaobj_nodes(void *cookie, const void *va, const void *vb)
39{
40 const struct nvkm_dmaobj *da = va;
41 const struct nvkm_dmaobj *db = vb;
42
43 if (da->handle < db->handle)
44 return -1;
45 if (da->handle > db->handle)
46 return +1;
47 return 0;
48}
49
50static int
51compare_dmaobj_key(void *cookie, const void *vo, const void *vk)
52{
53 const struct nvkm_dmaobj *d = vo;
54 const u64 *k = vk;
55
56 if (d->handle < *k)
57 return -1;
58 if (d->handle > *k)
59 return +1;
60 return 0;
61}
62
63const rb_tree_ops_t nvkm_client_dmatree_ops = {
64 .rbto_compare_nodes = compare_dmaobj_nodes,
65 .rbto_compare_key = compare_dmaobj_key,
66 .rbto_node_offset = offsetof(struct nvkm_dmaobj, rb),
67};
68#endif
69
70struct nvkm_dmaobj *
71nvkm_dma_search(struct nvkm_dma *dma, struct nvkm_client *client, u64 object)
72{
73#ifdef __NetBSD__
74 return rb_tree_find_node(&client->dmatree, &object);
75#else
76 struct rb_node *node = client->dmaroot.rb_node;
77 while (node) {
78 struct nvkm_dmaobj *dmaobj =
79 container_of(node, typeof(*dmaobj), rb);
80 if (object < dmaobj->handle)
81 node = node->rb_left;
82 else
83 if (object > dmaobj->handle)
84 node = node->rb_right;
85 else
86 return dmaobj;
87 }
88 return NULL;
89#endif
90}
91
92static int
93nvkm_dma_oclass_new(struct nvkm_device *device,
94 const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass, void *data, u32 size,
95 struct nvkm_object **pobject)
96{
97 struct nvkm_dma *dma = nvkm_dma(oclass->engine);
98 struct nvkm_dmaobj *dmaobj = NULL;
99 struct nvkm_client *client = oclass->client;
100#ifdef __NetBSD__
101 struct nvkm_dmaobj *collision;
102#else
103 struct rb_node **ptr = &client->dmaroot.rb_node;
104 struct rb_node *parent = NULL;
105#endif
106 int ret;
107
108 ret = dma->func->class_new(dma, oclass, data, size, &dmaobj);
109 if (dmaobj)
110 *pobject = &dmaobj->object;
111 if (ret)
112 return ret;
113
114 dmaobj->handle = oclass->object;
115
116#ifdef __NetBSD__
117 collision = rb_tree_insert_node(&client->dmatree, dmaobj);
118 if (collision != dmaobj)
119 /* XXX Don't we have to free this? */
120 return -EEXIST;
121 dmaobj->on_tree = true;
122#else
123 while (*ptr) {
124 struct nvkm_dmaobj *obj = container_of(*ptr, typeof(*obj), rb);
125 parent = *ptr;
126 if (dmaobj->handle < obj->handle)
127 ptr = &parent->rb_left;
128 else
129 if (dmaobj->handle > obj->handle)
130 ptr = &parent->rb_right;
131 else
132 return -EEXIST;
133 }
134
135 rb_link_node(&dmaobj->rb, parent, ptr);
136 rb_insert_color(&dmaobj->rb, &client->dmaroot);
137#endif
138 return 0;
139}
140
141static const struct nvkm_device_oclass
142nvkm_dma_oclass_base = {
143 .ctor = nvkm_dma_oclass_new,
144};
145
146static int
147nvkm_dma_oclass_fifo_new(const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass, void *data, u32 size,
148 struct nvkm_object **pobject)
149{
150 return nvkm_dma_oclass_new(oclass->engine->subdev.device,
151 oclass, data, size, pobject);
152}
153
154static const struct nvkm_sclass
155nvkm_dma_sclass[] = {
156 { 0, 0, NV_DMA_FROM_MEMORY, NULL, nvkm_dma_oclass_fifo_new },
157 { 0, 0, NV_DMA_TO_MEMORY, NULL, nvkm_dma_oclass_fifo_new },
158 { 0, 0, NV_DMA_IN_MEMORY, NULL, nvkm_dma_oclass_fifo_new },
159};
160
161static int
162nvkm_dma_oclass_base_get(struct nvkm_oclass *sclass, int index,
163 const struct nvkm_device_oclass **class)
164{
165 const int count = ARRAY_SIZE(nvkm_dma_sclass);
166 if (index < count) {
167 const struct nvkm_sclass *oclass = &nvkm_dma_sclass[index];
168 sclass->base = oclass[0];
169 sclass->engn = oclass;
170 *class = &nvkm_dma_oclass_base;
171 return index;
172 }
173 return count;
174}
175
176static int
177nvkm_dma_oclass_fifo_get(struct nvkm_oclass *oclass, int index)
178{
179 const int count = ARRAY_SIZE(nvkm_dma_sclass);
180 if (index < count) {
181 oclass->base = nvkm_dma_sclass[index];
182 return index;
183 }
184 return count;
185}
186
187static void *
188nvkm_dma_dtor(struct nvkm_engine *engine)
189{
190 return nvkm_dma(engine);
191}
192
193static const struct nvkm_engine_func
194nvkm_dma = {
195 .dtor = nvkm_dma_dtor,
196 .base.sclass = nvkm_dma_oclass_base_get,
197 .fifo.sclass = nvkm_dma_oclass_fifo_get,
198};
199
200int
201nvkm_dma_new_(const struct nvkm_dma_func *func, struct nvkm_device *device,
202 int index, struct nvkm_dma **pdma)
203{
204 struct nvkm_dma *dma;
205
206 if (!(dma = *pdma = kzalloc(sizeof(*dma), GFP_KERNEL)))
207 return -ENOMEM;
208 dma->func = func;
209
210 return nvkm_engine_ctor(&nvkm_dma, device, index,
211 0, true, &dma->engine);
212}
